a couple of players

03:27.772 --> 03:30.471
I invited out here
to compete in some tournaments.

03:30.514 --> 03:32.777
I'm responsible for
the transportation,

03:32.821 --> 03:35.258
the food, the hotel,
and location that we go,

03:35.302 --> 03:38.000
because I know the ropes,
because I've been through it.

03:38.043 --> 03:40.263
Playing professionally,
you know, that's --

03:40.307 --> 03:42.309
that's the main goal
for these newbies

03:42.352 --> 03:43.397
that's coming here, man.

03:51.013 --> 03:54.190
Oh, okay.

03:54.234 --> 03:57.585
I had a pretty good
high-school career, man.

03:57.628 --> 04:00.065
I got a couple scholarships
and stuff like that,

04:00.109 --> 04:02.459
but I blew my knee out,

04:02.503 --> 04:05.288
and my option was I could rehab,

04:05.332 --> 04:07.986
but I'm continuing to have
problems with it,

04:08.030 --> 04:09.640
or give up basketball.

04:09.684 --> 04:14.819
And, of course, I'm not
gonna say no to basketball.

04:14.863 --> 04:20.303
Then I found out they have these
tournaments in Mexico for cash.

04:20.347 --> 04:24.525
So I've been playing
here for about...

04:24.568 --> 04:27.092
11 years off and on,
you know, but...

04:27.136 --> 04:29.225
These new guys might think
they gonna walk right in

04:29.269 --> 04:31.227
and just win games easy.

04:31.271 --> 04:32.794
"Oh, we Americans," you know?

04:32.837 --> 04:34.970
"Who's better than Americans,"
you know?

04:35.013 --> 04:36.406
So it's a lot of pressure

04:36.450 --> 04:38.713
because I do have
a reputation online.

04:38.756 --> 04:41.368
If they don't play well, they're
gonna contact someone else

04:41.411 --> 04:42.630
to put a team together.

04:42.673 --> 04:48.331
Just hope for the best.

04:48.375 --> 04:50.377
-So, what you with y'all, man?
-What's up, Tim?

04:50.420 --> 04:51.595
-Khalil, right?
-What's up?

04:51.639 --> 04:52.857
-What's up, man?
-How you doing?

04:52.901 --> 04:54.250
Nice to meet you, dog.
You ready?

04:54.294 --> 04:55.904
I got a lot of pressure.
I ain't gonna lie.

04:55.947 --> 04:57.732
You know what I'm saying?
So they'll be some pro players

04:57.775 --> 04:59.299
playing in these tournaments.
-Oh, yeah.

04:59.342 --> 05:01.344
-Yeah, invite, so...
-Oh, yeah, I already know.

05:01.388 --> 05:02.737
...they -- they gonna
know y'all new,

05:02.780 --> 05:04.565
you know what I'm saying?
So they're gonna

05:04.608 --> 05:06.697
come at your knee, and they
going physical everything, man,

05:06.741 --> 05:10.353
and I got pressure on 'em
because I hyped it up to the guy

05:10.397 --> 05:11.963
that actually put us
in the tournament.

05:12.007 --> 05:14.749
Man, I got to impress him.
You know what I'm saying?

05:14.792 --> 05:16.403
And so it's some -- it's some --
it's some pressure on me.

05:16.446 --> 05:17.491
It's some pressure on me.

05:17.534 --> 05:19.362
Khalil: I'm from New York City.

05:19.406 --> 05:21.190
I'm from Queens.

05:21.233 --> 05:23.845
I made a name in college,
and everybody,

05:23.888 --> 05:25.847
you know, figured like,
"Oh, Khalil's gonna be a pro.

05:25.890 --> 05:27.631
Yeah, yeah.
You a pro prospect."

05:27.675 --> 05:30.373
But I was living reckless,
going to parties.

05:30.417 --> 05:32.332
My mind was all over.

05:32.375 --> 05:36.988
I was just living foolishly,
but here goes my second chance.

05:37.032 --> 05:38.729
I really want a contract.

05:38.773 --> 05:41.036
Right now I have the opportunity
to make something of myself.

05:41.079 --> 05:42.907
That's what I'm gonna do.

05:42.951 --> 05:45.083
Tim: We missing one, man.
Xay.

05:45.127 --> 05:46.737
Y'all know he missed
the flight, right?

05:49.479 --> 05:52.395
Yeah. Well, we gonna go to
the bus station right now.

05:52.439 --> 05:54.179
We going there,
you know what I'm saying?

05:54.223 --> 05:55.877
And we'll wait for him, and we
tell him how to get there,

05:55.920 --> 05:57.444
and then when he get there, man,

05:57.487 --> 05:59.750
you're gonna try and look out
for him, you know?

05:59.794 --> 06:01.361
Yeah.

06:01.404 --> 06:11.240
♪♪

06:11.283 --> 06:13.416
Come on, man.
I'm gonna rough you up. Ohh.

06:13.460 --> 06:15.853
I'm gonna rough you up.
Ohh!

06:15.897 --> 06:19.901
♪♪

06:19.944 --> 06:22.294
Make it.

06:22.338 --> 06:24.645
Unh! Let's go. Good shot.
Let's go.

06:24.688 --> 06:28.388
Good shot, man.
Give me five.

06:28.431 --> 06:31.303
You got to get
some rhythm, son.

06:31.347 --> 06:34.263
Right now I'm just preparing,
getting ready to catch

06:34.306 --> 06:36.831
this flight, man,
make it over there to Mexico.

06:36.874 --> 06:39.181
I'm going down there
to play tournament ball.

06:39.224 --> 06:41.792
I'm not going down there to play
in a league or anything.

06:41.836 --> 06:45.143
You play ball, you win
a tournament, you get paid.

06:45.187 --> 06:47.015
You got first, second,
and third place.

06:47.058 --> 06:48.625
I wish I could have
went to the NBA,

06:48.669 --> 06:52.586
but because of the decisions
I've made upon myself,

06:52.629 --> 06:54.414
you know, I hindered myself.

06:54.457 --> 06:56.764
I got a lot of recognition
from high school.

06:56.807 --> 06:58.809
"Mr. Basketball,"
number one in the state,

06:58.853 --> 07:01.812
uh, Dandy's Dozen,
McDonald All-American nominee,

07:01.856 --> 07:04.119
Reebok All-American.

07:04.162 --> 07:07.122
I didn't make the GPA I needed,
so I had to go DII,

07:07.165 --> 07:10.952
and I got into all, you know,
little bullshit troubles,

07:10.995 --> 07:13.824
team fights, getting in trouble
and shit at school.

07:13.868 --> 07:16.653
I left there, and, uh,
now I got to do this,

07:16.697 --> 07:18.307
go back-and-forth
and play in tournaments,

07:18.350 --> 07:20.657
you know, just try to provide
for my family, you know?

07:20.701 --> 07:23.660
Uh, I could always get a job
somewhere over here,

07:23.704 --> 07:26.576
but it wouldn't be the same.
You know, I hate settling.

07:26.620 --> 07:28.404
There's all type of
regular motherfuckers,

07:28.448 --> 07:30.624
but I'm extraordinary, God damn.

07:30.667 --> 07:38.370
[ Fireworks whistling,
exploding ]

07:38.414 --> 07:40.547
There you go! I knew --

07:40.590 --> 07:43.288
I better get my money worth.

07:43.332 --> 07:45.508
♪♪

07:45.552 --> 07:48.032
Just a little something. It
ain't nothing major, you know?

07:48.076 --> 07:51.079
I try.
I got to say, man, I just --

07:51.122 --> 07:53.211
I just work hard so I can see
everybody else happy.

07:53.255 --> 07:56.388
You know, I want to be happy,
too, but, you see.

07:56.432 --> 07:59.479
I got a lot riding on this.
I got three kids.

07:59.522 --> 08:01.306
Well, I'm leaving
behind my family.

08:01.350 --> 08:03.700
Best-case scenario,
should I come back

08:03.744 --> 08:06.181
with at least
three wrecks, $3,000.

08:06.224 --> 08:08.531
[ Chuckles ]

08:08.575 --> 08:13.275
I'm just trying to do something
I can make enough money for.

08:13.318 --> 08:25.766
♪♪

08:25.809 --> 08:35.166
